reviewText:
Doesn't seem to teach what I wanted.  It covers all the basics that I already know but I want to know how to enter coordinates from books.
It tells how to edit coordinates, but:
What position format do I use?  What map datum?

I have an older Garmin 76 and the new 78Sc has much better reception by far. It even finds satillites from inside my home. The old 76 could not even receive through a few tree limbs or on cloudy days. They both float and since I use it on my boat and for geocaching the 78Sc is ideal. Wonderful unit. It came with the shore area map and then this tiny stick added the entire NA streets so I have both.
